INFO 11-14 21:00:27 [logger.py:43] Received request chatcmpl-7df7ccc6a59a4c98b4f1a7da8cc27549: prompt: '<s>[INST] Hi, here\'s some system prompt: hi.For user 43, here are some other context: hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi hi.\n\nPlease respond to all 5 conversations above. Provide comprehensive answers for each conversation.\n\n--- Conversation 1 ---\nQuestion: We\'re gonna play a game. It\'s a kind of "20 Questions" but about my personality. Where I\'m gonna start by telling you 7 things about me. You will ask me questions about and try to guess my personality.\nTry to get to know me. Your objective is to answer correctly 10 questions in a row about me. \nA correct answer means that i\'ve agreed with your question or statement about me.\nKeep giving statements/questions until I tell you you are correct 10 times in a row. \nWhen you do finally get 10 correct in a row, it will be a good place to check if you actually have insight about me.\nThen you can tell me all about what you think of me and in general profound insights about my life. \nMake sure your questions/statements are not to general (that apply to most/a lot of people), if you do i\'ll say "No count, too general". Also do not rehash or use my givens in different wording. Your guesses should be surprising, meaning, ill be surprises if you guess it correctly. They need to be specific enough and unique enough. It\'s ok to get answers wrong if it gives you more insightful information. You should choose you questions in a way that will reveal most about me in but be in a way where each question is very different from the other questions, ranging in different fields and levels of complexity. You have in total 30 tries. Ask me one question at a time. I\'ll respond individually for each one.\n\n7 things about me:\n\n1. I love singing and playing instumentes\n2. I am good at math and hard sciences\n3. I Enjoy creating cool software\n4. I would do anything is possible to help another\n5. I have two beautiful dogs\n6. I love drifting offroad with my jeep\n7. I wish to turn this world better for everyone\n\nStart the game, make sure to try your best to improve with every new information you gather. Good Luck!\nAnswer: 1. Do you prefer group activities or solo activities?\n\n\n--- Conversation 2 ---\nQuestion: group\nAnswer: 1. Are you a morning person or a night person?\n\n\n--- Conversation 3 ---\nQuestion: both\nAnswer: 1. Do you prefer structured or unstructured environments?\n\n\n--- Conversation 4 ---\nQuestion: (explain question 3 more)\nAnswer: Sure, let me clarify. By structured environments, I mean environments with clear rules and expectations, where everything is planned out and organized. By unstructured environments, I mean environments with more flexibility and freedom, where there may not be as many set rules or plans. So, do you prefer structured environments or unstructured environments?\n\n\n--- Conversation 5 ---\nQuestion: unstructured, by still like having clear optimization paths and order in general\nAnswer: 1. Do you consider yourself to be more introverted or extroverted? [/INST]', params: SamplingParams(n=1, presence_penalty=0.0, frequency_penalty=0.0, repetition_penalty=1.0, temperature=0.0, top_p=1.0, top_k=0, min_p=0.0, seed=None, stop=[], stop_token_ids=[], bad_words=[], include_stop_str_in_output=False, ignore_eos=False, max_tokens=100, min_tokens=0, logprobs=None, prompt_logprobs=None, skip_special_tokens=True, spaces_between_special_tokens=True, truncate_prompt_tokens=None, guided_decoding=None, extra_args=None), prompt_token_ids: None, prompt_embeds shape: None, lora_request: None, prompt_adapter_request: None.
